<HEADLINE> Indian Foreign Secretary Arrives in Dhaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Indian Foreign Secretary K.
Raghunath arrived here Sunday on a two-day visit to Bangladesh
following a visit to India by Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina earlier
this month.
</P>
<P>
Raghunath is scheduled to hold talks Monday with his
Bangladeshi counterpart Mustafizur Rahman on bilateral issues as
well as regional and international issues of mutual concern,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
"The agenda of the routine consultation between the two foreign
secretaries is open," a senior official with the Foreign Office
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Indian foreign secretary is also expected to meet with
Hasina and Foreign Minister Abdus Samad Azad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
