<HEADLINE> Holbrooke Says Kosovo War Looms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 28 (Xinhua) -- U.S. presidential envoy for Cyprus
Richard Holbrooke has warned the crisis in Serbia's southern
province of Kosovo could develop into war.
</P>
<P>
Describing the Kosovo situation as "explosive", Holbrook told
the Athens newspaper "To Vima" on Sunday that clashes between
Belgrade and the ethnic Albanians seeking independence from
Yugoslavia could "at any moment develop into war".
</P>
<P>
The Kosovo war, the envoy said, if spread, could bring Greece at
the doorstep of its own involvement in the crisis.
</P>
<P>
While calling for a peaceful resolution to the Kosovo crisis,
Holbrook said the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) would
not rule out military means to end the problem.
</P>
<P>
At least 300 people, most of them being women, children and the
elderly, have been killed in the conflict since February.
</P>
<P>
The presidential envoy siad that the peaceful resolution of the
Kosovo crisis through a change in the status of the region, but
within the present borders of Yugoslavia, was perferable, but
warned that if necessary, the NATO would not sit idle, as in the
case of Bosnia early in the decade.
</P>
<P>
Belgrade has refused any external intervention into the Kosovo,
saying it a domestic affair. 
</P>
</TEXT>
