<HEADLINE> Laurent Blanc Scores First World Cup Golden Goal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LENS, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Laurent Blanc scored the first ever
golden goal in the World Cup finals to give France a hard-fought 1-0
victory over Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
The match went into the extra time when the two teams played to a
goalless tie after 90-minute regulation time and Blanc scored the
goal at the 110th minute to put the host team through. 
</P>
</TEXT>
