<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Edge Paraguay Through Golden Goal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LENS, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Host team France needed 110 minutes and a
golden goal to beat the tough Paraguay team in a World Cup round of 16
match on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The French team went into the game as the favorites and they did
enjoy great advantage during the match.
</P>
<P>
But without their star playmaker Zinedine Zidane due to
suspension, the French team could not play their passing game
effectively and failed to convert any of the scoring chances.
</P>
<P>
Thierry Henry could have put France 1-0 ahead at the 39th minute
but his shot hit the bar and rolled outside.
</P>
<P>
The French goal-keeper Fabien Barthez was also forced to put up
several saves by the Paraguay counter-attacks.
</P>
<P>
After the regulation time, the French team launched desperate
attacks on the Paraguay goal, expecially when the game was near its
end. Blanc slamed home a heading pass from David Trezeguet at the
110th minute to put the host team through to the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
The goal is the first ever golden goal in the history of World
Cup finals since FIFA adopted the "sudden death" rule for the first
time in World Cup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
