<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chirac Arrives in Maputo, Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, June 28 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
Sunday afternoon arrived here from South Africa for a two-day
state visit to strengthen ties with Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
This is Chirac's first visit to Mozambique since it gained
independence in 1975 and the third leg of Chirac' s four-nation
African tour aimed at opening up relations with non-French
speaking countries in Southern Africa.
</P>
<P>
Chirac's delegation which includes Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine and Minister of Trade Jacques Dondoux and 230 Businessmen
was met at the airport by Mozambican senior officials including
President Joaquim Chissano.
</P>
<P>
According to the agenda, Chirac will meet Sunday with Afonso
Dhlakama, Chairman of the Mozambican National Resistance, the
biggest opposition party in the country.
</P>
<P>
He will lay a wreath on the Heroes' Monument here, tour the
French cultural center in downtown Maputo and sponsor the naming
ceremony of the "French Street" before signing several agreements
on cooperation with Mozambique Monday.
</P>
<P>
Paris has been maintaining cooperative ties with Maputo in the
fields of Railway, electricity, tele-communications and the basic
infrastructure like water supplies, and in mine-clearing, health
and culture, among others.
</P>
<P>
France provides Mozambique with 40 million French Francs or
less than seven million U.S. Dollars annually in aid apart from
giving Maputo preferential loans.
</P>
<P>
The French guests will leave here for Luanda, Angola on Sunday
afternoon to continue their African trip. 
</P>
</TEXT>
