<HEADLINE> England to Count on Players' Experience: Hoddle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LA BAULE, France, June 28 (Xinhua) -- England will win their second
round game over Argentina with their edge on players' experiece, coach
Glenn Hoddle said here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"Experience will count a lot in the second round and especially in
the game against Argentina," said Hoddle.
</P>
<P>
The coache said he did not consider it as an opportunity to revenge
their loss to Argentina on the well-known Diego Maradona hand-ball.
</P>
<P>
"I don't want to talk about revenge, especially about Maradona in
the '86 match, when he won the game with his famous hand-ball," he
said.
</P>
<P>
"I'd simply like to redress the balance - I'm still convinced that
Argentina wouldn't have won 2-0 without this golden hand-ball," he
added.
</P>
<P>
Hoddle said he was fully aware of Argentines' ability to control
the flow of the game, which will be held in Saint Etienne on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"We know Argentina has some real fighters, who are able to control
of the game and then speed suddenly." 
</P>
</TEXT>
