<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-28 20:28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece Never to Stop Supporting Cyprus: President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Greek President Costis
Stefanopoulos said on Sunday that his country would never stop
supporting Cyprus in its efforts to regain integrity, and
safeguard freedom and independence.
</P>
<P>
Before leaving Cyprus at Larnaca airport after a four-day
visit, Stefanopoulos told reporters that "the Cyprus problem is
Greece's top priority."
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has remained divided since 1974 when Turkey landed its
troops and took over the northern third of the Mediterranean
island to protect the Turkish Cypriot minorities after a failed
coup by the Greek Cypriots seeking union with Greece.
</P>
<P>
The Greek president stressed that during his visit, he tried to
send "a message of friendship and reconciliation" to Turkey. He
voiced hope that Ankara will listen to it.
</P>
<P>
Greece and Turkey, both members of the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization, have long been at odds with each other over, among
other things, the issue of Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Stefanopoulos said that apart from Turkey and Turkish Cypriots,
he also tried to send a message to the international community.
</P>
<P>
"I wanted to stress the great responsibility of the
international community for Cyprus, because it has not done what
it should and could have done for justice in Cyprus," he said.
</P>
<P>
The world community, including the United Nations, has been
striving to help reunify the island in a bizonal and bicommunal
formula. But so far, no tangible results have been achieved.
</P>
<P>
Seeing Stefanopoulos off at the airport, Cypriot President
Glafcos Clerides stressed that the people of Cyprus have realized
that "Greece and Cyprus walk together and will fight from the same
trenches for justice."
</P>
<P>
The Greek Cypriots have also realized that "there is close
cooperation between the governments of Greece and Cyprus and
between their political leaders," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We all stand on one point: that we will fight for freedom,
democracy and the rights not only of Greek Cypriots but also those
of our Turkish Cypriot compatriots," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
