<HEADLINE> Denmark Reach Quarterfinals in World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAINT-DENIS, France, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Denmark reached the last
eight in the World Cup finals by beating Nigeria 4-1 at Stade de
France here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Denmark will meet defending champions Brazil in the quarterfinals
in Nantes on July 3.
</P>
<P>
Striker Peter Moller put the former European champions ahead only
three minutes into the game, slotting the ball home past Nigerian
keeper Peter Rufai after receiving a pass from Ajax Amsterdam striker
Michael Laudrup.
</P>
<P>
Moller, who plays with Dutch club PSV Eindhoven, was also involved
in the second Denmark goal when he blasted a powerful free kick in the
12th minute.
</P>
<P>
Rufai parried it out but Brian Laudrup, Michael's younger brother,
surged ahead to score in the box, making it 3-0 for Denmark before
break.
</P>
<P>
Ebbe Sand scored what could be the fastest goal for a substitute in
the competition so far by tapping home a Michael Laudrup pass less
than 30 seconds after stepping onto the pitch in the 60th minute.
</P>
<P>
Udinese midfielder Thomas Helveg netted the fourth Danish goal from
within the box in the 76th minute but Nigeria answered two minute
later with a goal from substitute midfielder Tijani Babangida.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria had a scoring chance in the 28th minute, when defender
Okechukwu Uche lobbed the ball over the bar after Peter Schmeichel
deflected a Nwankwo Kanu header.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Jay-Jay Okocha squandered opportunities twice in a span
of six minutes when he shot the ball over the bar in 33rd and 39th
minutes.
</P>
<P>
Schmeichel was kept busy in the last ten minutes of the game when
the Nigerians rallied strongly.
</P>
<P>
Both Rasheed Yekini and Okocha shot the ball too high. 
</P>
</TEXT>
