<HEADLINE> Martin Enters Fourth Round in Wimbledon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WIMBLEDON, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Todd Martin of the United States
claimed a four set victory over Australian Todd Woodbridge to
reached the fourth-round showdown with either twice-finalist Goran
Ivanisevic of Croatia or Daniel Vacek of the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
Martin scored 6-4, 4-6, 7-6 (7/1), 6-4 in a resumed match held
up by rain on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It is the fifth time Martin, twice a semi-finalist but missed
last year's Wimbledon with a Knee injury, has reached the fourth
round of the Championships in six visits.
</P>
<P>
16-year-old Serena Williams was forced to bow out of her match
against Spain's Virginia Ruano Pascual. Williams, her left calf
heavily strapped, limped off court while trailing 5-7, 1-4.
</P>
<P>
Ruano Pacual's win snuffed out a possible fourth-round clash
between Serena and her 17-year-old seventh-seeded sister Venus
Williams.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old Spaniard had won only one match in three
previous visits here before this year's tournament.
</P>
<P>
Spain's fifth-seeded compatriot Arantxa Sanchez Vicario
recovered from another slow start to beat Austria's Sylvia
Pliuschke 7-5, 6-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
