<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Bank Opens Beijing Branch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Banque Nationale de Paris
(BNP) officially opened its Beijing branch here today.
</P>
<P>
BNP is one of the world's leading international banks with more
than 2,000 branches and 60,000 corporate customers worldwide. It
ranks as the top French bank in serving large corporations and
financing international trade.
</P>
<P>
Addressing today's opening ceremony, Levy-Garboua, chief
executive of international banking and finance of BNP, said that
BNP's business presence in China dates back to 1860. In the 1960s
it became a correspondent bank of the Bank of China and set up
representative offices in Beijing, Guangzhou, Shanghai and
Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
BNP has developed close links with major Chinese banks and
corporations, particularly as they were expanding abroad, he said.
</P>
<P>
Levy-Garboua said BNP has built a strong presence in China with
four fully operational branches in Shenzhen, Tianjin, Guangzhou
and Beijing, as well as two representative offices in Shanghai and
Chengdu.
</P>
<P>
During the last 15 years, BNP's total commitment to China has
been constantly growing, he said. The bank has participated in the
financing of such major projects in China as Daya Bay nuclear
power station and the Three Gorges Dam. BNP also is one of the
major financing institutions for the country's airline and
shipping companies.
</P>
<P>
"BNP has been a major investor in China over the past few years
and this branch in the capital was a very important step for our
organization," he said.
</P>
<P>
"As evidenced by our past and present achievements, our
strategy in China is not opportunistic. We have a clear and strong
willingness to expand our activities in this country with a view
to the long term, because we believe in its extraordinary
potential and bright future." 
</P>
</TEXT>
