<HEADLINE> China's Real Estate Business Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- China's real estate sector
continued to climb in May after it bottomed out in April, the
State Statistics Bureau and the China Business Climate Monitoring
Center reported today.
</P>
<P>
The China Real Estate Business Climate Index stood at 101.68
points in May, up 0.78 points from April or 3.83 points from the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
During the first five months of this year, real estate
investment increased by 15.2 percent on an annual basis, ranking
first among various fixed-asset investments.
</P>
<P>
New construction maintained a rapid growth of 41.4 percent to
become a major driving force in the index's rise.  
