<P>
During their talks, Presidents Yeltsin and Kwasniewski
discussed the problem of links between mainland Russia and its
region of Kaliningrad, separated by Poland and Lithuania, and the
construction of the London-Paris-Berlin-Warsaw-Minsk-Moscow
highway.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents agreed that youth contacts between the two
countries must be expanded. They hailed the idea of setting up a
joint presidents' fund to support such contacts.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed the Kosovo situation and ways to solve the
crisis there.
</P>
<P>
Kwasniewski confirmed an invitation to Yeltsin to make an
official visit to Poland in the second half of December. The
invitation was accepted by the Russian president. 
</P>
</TEXT>
