<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Banks Increase Support for Infrastructure Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- China's banking sector has been
adopting active measures this year in support of infrastructure
construction.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the People's Bank of China (PBOC) said that banks
have raised their efficiency in appraising new projects, while key
state construction projects and enterprise retooling projects are
receiving loans directly from bank headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The headquarters of all the commercial banks also strengthened
their capital control and unified credit management to ensure the
capital demand of infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
PBOC sources said that the growth rate of infrastructure loans
this year is clearly higher than that of other loans. By the end
of May, the State Development Bank has already finished its
full-year railway investment plan of 16.35 billion yuan (1.97
billion US dollars), and Construction Bank has extended railway
loans of 6 billion yuan (723 million US dollars), accounting for
85 percent of its plan for the year.
</P>
<P>
In regard to highway loans, Industrial and Commercial Bank,
Agricultural Bank and Construction Bank have extended loans of
57.9 billion yuan (7 billion US dollars) by the end of May to
support 140 projects.
</P>
<P>
The banks have handled the relationship between financial risk
control and the support for economic development well, the PBOC
sources said, adding that the banks have been extending loans
strictly according to credit rules.  
</P>
</TEXT>
