<HEADLINE> Construction Begins on Bridge Linking Macao, Zhuhai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Construction began today on a
bridge linking Macao and Zhuhai, a city in south China's Guangdong
Province.
</P>
<P>
The 1.4-kilometer bridge, named the "Lotus Bridge," will cost
200 million yuan. The cost will be evenly shared by the
governments of Macao and Zhuhai, one of China's Special Economic
Zones.
</P>
<P>
The two-way bridge, scheduled to be completed before Macao's
handover to China in 1999, will have six lanes and be
capable of handling 10 million vehicles annually.
</P>
<P>
The regional governments of Macao and Zhuhai have both agreed
that the completion of the bridge will tighten the links between
the two sides and play a positive role in promoting Macao's future
prosperity and development. 
</P>
