<HEADLINE> Some 50,000 Congolese Refugees Return Home from </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 29 (Xinhua) -- At least 48,658 refugees
from the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) have left Tanzania
for home since last September as the latest trip by ship was made
Friday.
</P>
<P>
A spokeswoman for the United Nations High Commissioner for
Refugees (UNHCR) Dar es Salaam Office said Monday that some
42,000 Congolese refugees still remain in Tanzania, waiting for
repatriation to their home country.
</P>
