<HEADLINE> China Marks 100th Anniversary of Liu Shaoqi's Birth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- China has published a collection
of photos and paintings to mark the 100th birth anniversary of
late Chinese President Liu Shaoqi.
</P>
<P>
The collection, including 100 photos and 100 paintings,
records the whole life of the great man, said Liu Zheng, a
participant at a forum celebrating the publication of the book. It
reflects the image and personality of Liu Shaoqi, he said.
</P>
<P>
More than 80 celebrities in the capital attended the forum and
saw an art exhibition that also described the real life of the
late leader.
</P>
<P>
Liu Shaoqi, born in Ningxiang County in central China's Hunan
Province on November 24, 1898, was president in the late 1950s
and early 1960s.
</P>
<P>
Liu has been hailed as a "public servant to the society" for
his honesty and battles against corruption.
</P>
<P>
The collection of photos and paintings was published by the
Qingdao Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
According to the forum, a large exhibition will be held
October 20 to mark the 100th anniversary of Liu's birth.  
</P>
