<HEADLINE> Chairman of AIG on His Company Group's Links with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai is one of the most
prospective metropolises in the world, according to Maurice
Greenberg, chairman and chief executive officer of American
International Group (AIG) of the United States.
</P>
<P>
As the head of one of the leading insurance companies in the
world, Greenberg has come to Shanghai almost on an annual basis
since he first visit to the city in 1975.
</P>
<P>
"I have had opportunities to witness big changes and
development process in Shanghai over recent years. So I believe it
is one of the most prospective cities in the world," he said.
</P>
<P>
As a founder of the Shanghai Mayor-International Entrepreneurs
Consulting Conference, Greenberg prompted his company to invest in
the largest U.S.-funded project in China in 1985. Moreover, AIG
provided funds for the development of a business center in
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
He has also personally experienced expansion of all-round
cooperation between AIG and Shanghai in such fields as culture,
medical care, scientific research, education and social welfare.
</P>
<P>
The American International Assurance (AIA), an subsidiary of
the AIG, has been the first foreign insurance company that
obtained an operational license in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Greenberg went on to say that he has special feelings toward
Shanghai and its people as AIG was founded in this city at early
this century. And he is one of the first group of foreign citizens
who became honorary citizens of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
In 1990, he was entrusted by the Shanghai Municipal Government
to hold a large-scale international forum on reviving Shanghai as
an international financial center.
</P>
<P>
AIA will introduce international vision and advanced management
system and technology of insurance business to Shanghai, so as to
help advance the growth of China's insurance market, he added.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Greenberg, an active advocator of maintaining normal
trade ties with China back in the United States, takes pride in
witnessing his company's interests growing in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
For the expansion of its insurance business, a brand-new AIA
tower mansion has been erected recently in the downtown financial
section along the Bund, where a group of magnificent
European-style architectures built by Western powers about a
century ago overlook the busy Huangpu River.  
</P>
</TEXT>
