<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Get Loan From Kuwait for Bridge Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will receive a
20-million-U.S.-dollar loan from Kuwait for a bridge project under
an agreement signed recently between the two sides, press reports
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Koarika-Shikarpur Bridge project is designed to connect the
center of Barisal division, 118 kilometers south of here, with the
capital city of Dhaka, and to improve the socio-economic
conditions of the country's southwestern part by building two
bridges and their access roads.
</P>
<P>
The project comprises the construction of the 234-meter-long
and 388-meter-long bridges over River Sandhya at Shikarpur and
Doarika of Barisal, and 12-kilometers of access roads.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be the 12th from the Kuwait Fund to Bangladesh.
</P>
