<HEADLINE> Chinese, Estonian Defense Ministers Hold Talks in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian, in talking with his Estonian counterpart Andrus Oovel
here today, said China is ready to work jointly with Estonia
toward friendly ties between the two nations and their armed
forces.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice-chairman of China's Central Military Commission,
said that since China and Estonia forged diplomatic ties, the two
countries have conducted frequent exchanges of high-level visits
and cooperated in areas of politics, economics, science and
technology, and culture.
</P>
<P>
He said Oovel is the first Estonian defense minister to visit
China, and cited his visit as a "major event" in Sino-Estonian
military relations, which could lay the foundation for the
development of such relations.
</P>
<P>
There are broad prospects and great potential for the
development of bilateral military ties, he said.
</P>
<P>
Chi also briefed the Estonian visitors on China's defense
policy and its armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Oovel said he is very glad to visit China and hopes his current
visit will promote exchanges and cooperation in various areas
between the armed forces of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Chi presided over a welcoming ceremony for
Oovel and his party, who arrived here earlier today at Chi's
invitation. Besides Beijing, Oovel and his party will also visit
Shanghai and Hangzhou. 
</P>
