<HEADLINE> Nigeria, Portugal Sign Liquefied Gas Supply Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria will supply 350 million
standard cubic meters of liquefied natural gas a year to
Portugal, starting from October 1999, the Post Express reported
Monday
</P>
<P>
The report said the Sale and Purchase Agreement was signed
Friday in Lisbon, Portugal, between the Nigeria Liquefied Natural
Gas (NLNG) Limited and the TRANSGAS company of Portugal.
</P>
<P>
The NLNG Limited is a joint venture between the Nigeria
National Petroleum Corporation and several foreign oil companies,
including Shell, Elf and Agip. Its total investment exceeds 3.6
billion U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The plant located on Bonny Island, Rivers State, in south
Nigeria, is expected to produce 7.15 billion stand cubic meters
of liquefied natural gas a year when it is fully commissioned
next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
