<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed mixed Monday as dealers said
investors were uncertain with the market's direction, but indices
held steady.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said investors were cautious and digesting the
Statutory Reserve Requirement (SRR) cut by two percentage points
to eight percent from 10 percent effective July 1, which was
announced by Bank Negara (State Bank) late Friday.
</P>
<P>
At the close Monday, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index
rose 5.10 points to 450.77, the all-share Emas Index added 0.67 of
a point to 114.56, the Industrial Index increased 7.35 points to
898.74 while the second board index eased 0.35 of a point to
98.30.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 286 to 234, while 169 counters were
unchanged and 233 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover fell to 114.110 million shares worth 215.653
million ringgit (about 51.7153 million U.S. dollars) from 131.668
million shares worth 265.606 million ringgit (about 63.6944
million dollars) on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover was lower at 109.621 million shares
worth 207.639 million ringgit (about 49.7935 million dollars) from
Friday's 126.212 million shares valued at 257.044 million ringgit
(about 61.6412 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover eased to 4.489 million shares worth
8.013 million ringgit (about 1.9215 million dollars) from 5.456
million shares valued at 8.562 million ringgit (about 2.0532
million dollars) on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Off market deals shed to 7.513 million shares worth 15.587
million ringgit (about 3.7378 million dollars) from 18.237 million
shares valued at 22.038 million ringgit (about 5.2848 million
dollars) on Friday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 7.265
million shares, industrial products 8.687 million shares,
construction 11.151 million shares, trading/services 41.355
million shares, infrastructure 848,000 million shares, finance
20.753 million shares, hotels 195,000 million shares, properties
9.744 million shares, plantation 3.239 million shares, mining
146,000 shares, trusts 100,000 shares, closed/fund 46,000 shares
and loans 6.091 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
