<HEADLINE> Stojkovic Says Yugoslavs Afraid of No One </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOULOUSE, France, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavian midfielder Dragan
Stojkovic has said his team would be afraid of no one in the World Cup
competition.
</P>
<P>
"With all due respect to our opponents, we're afraid of no one and
we hope to go further in the competition than we did in 1990," said
Stojkovic, whose team will face the Netherlands in Municipal Stadium
here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Stojkovic, who plays for Grampus Eight, added: "The match against
the Netherlands should be a spectacular one. The two teams have
interesting styles, which make the confrontation exciting, both for
the players and for the spectators."
</P>
<P>
Stojkovic said, "It has to be said that those two teams play a
similiar game. I hope we will win and go on to the Velodrome Stadium
in Marseille (for the quarterfinals)... It would be amazing if we
could get through to the semifinals."
</P>
<P>
Teammate Pedrag Mijatovic said the match would be a difficult one.
</P>
<P>
"We're not the favorites, but we do have a very competitive team,"
said the Real Madrid striker.
</P>
<P>
"We are capable of great things. Our qualification matches enabled
us to improve our game and we will show that our skills can take us
through to the quarter-finals," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
