<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Complete Strike Witnessed in India's Ganganagar Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Normal life in Ganganagar town
of Jaipur city, 280 km southwest of New Delhi, was disrupted
Monday in the wake of a complete strike.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that business centers and shops
remained closed and public transport was off the roads of the town
of Rajasthan State. Two companies of the Rajasthan armed
constabulary were deployed in the city to maintain law and order.
No untoward incident has been reported so far.
</P>
<P>
The town witnessed arson and pitched battle between protesters
and police Saturday when the former held a demonstration demanding
improved civic amenities.
</P>
<P>
The strike was called by all major opposition parties in
protest against Saturday's violence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
