<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. President, Mrs. Clinton Leave Beijing for Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton, Mrs.
Clinton and his official delegation completed his three-day visit
in Beijing and left for Shanghai later today.
</P>
<P>
President Clinton visited the prestigious Beijing University
this morning, where he addressed a gathering of students and
faculty on the campus and then donated more than 500 books to the
university's new library, the largest of its kind in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. president and Mrs. Clinton arrived in Beijing last
Friday evening after a one-day trip to the ancient city of Xi'an
in northwest China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
During the past three days in Beijing, President Clinton held
the summit with his Chinese counterpart Jiang Zemin on Saturday.
The two leaders also met the press after their talks.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, President Clinton and his family toured the Palace
Museum or the imperial Forbidden City, the former residence of
China's imperial families during the Ming (1368-1644) and Qing
(1644-1911) dynasties, and the Great Wall, China's most famous
landmark, which is known as one of the world's eight wonders.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
