<HEADLINE> Mozambique Needs Two Million Tons of Grain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique needs about two million
tons of grain in the 1998-99 year, going beyond the country's
estimated yield of about 1.618 million tons in the year.
</P>
<P>
A report from the Mozambique Internal Trade Bureau said that
1.74 million tons of the two million tons are to for the citizens
daily consumption, while the rest is for industrial and other uses.
</P>
<P>
Giving to the consideration to stock, the report said that the
country is in 196,000 tons short supply of grain in the year.
</P>
<P>
Monday's Noticias daily said that the country will have to
import about 116,000 to 136,000 tons of rice, and 130,000 to
160,000 tons of wheat.
</P>
<P>
While 70,000 tons of corn is needed for three Mozambican
southern provinces including Maputo, over 120,000 tons of corn is
to be exported in the north, said the paper.  
</P>
</TEXT>
