<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uganda Gets Foreign Aid in Fighting Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Uganda has received 8.3 million U.S.
Dollars in aid from Egypt which has decided to help fight the water
hyacinth in Lake Victoria and its spread down the Nile River.
</P>
<P>
Mohammed Ashmawy, the Charge d'Affairs of the Egyptian
embassy to Uganda, was quoted Monday by the East African weekly as saying
that the modalities for disbursing the money are being finalized.
</P>
<P>
"The money has been offered to Uganda, it is up to the government
to decide whether they want to share it with Kenya and Tanzania in
the spirit of East African cooperation," he said.
</P>
<P>
Uganda, Kenya and Tanzania which share the Lake Victoria have
agreed to fight jointly for the elimination and control of the weed
because the wind keeps blowing it from one place to another.
</P>
<P>
The three East African countries have formed a Lake Victoria
Fisheries Organization based in Jinja, some 80 kms east of Kampala
city, to preserve the lake's eco-system.
</P>
<P>
The water hyacinth on the lake has been hampering the operations
of hydro-electric power plants and fishering activities.
</P>
<P>
In Uganda alone, an estimated 2,000 to 4,000 hectares of the lake
shoreline and bays are infested with the weed, with the lake
containing more than 1.25 million metric tonnes of the weed.
</P>
<P>
Lake Victoria is the main source of livelihood for more than 40
million people in the region and the River Nile, which is partly
covered by the weed, serves as a major source of water for
drinking and irrigation in Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The weed reportedly covers 599 kms of the banks of the longest
river in Africa.
</P>
<P>
The weed had brought the business of some landing sites to a halt
and is blamed for the unexplained deaths of fish. It also makes
Uganda's Electricity Board lose 2,700 dollar each month by
interfering with the power generation at the Owen Falls Dam in Jinja.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980629.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
