<HEADLINE> Outgoing Cuban Ambassador Hails Friendship with </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The out-going Cuban
ambassador to Tanzania, Arnando Entralgo, has hailed the good
co-operation between the two governments in social, economic and
political sectors.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Entralgo praised the friendship of the two
countries at a farewell ceremony held for him here Sunday after
his four years stay in Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The state-owned Daily News, in a front page report on Monday,
quoted the outgoing ambassador as saying that despite the
external pressure imposed on Cuba, his country will not fail to
provide essential support to needy countries while ensuring its
