<HEADLINE> China Has New Plans For Two Oil Giants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- In early July, China will reform
its petroleum sector, starting with the China National Petroleum
Corp (CNPC) and China National Petrochemical (Sinopec).
</P>
<P>
The names will remain unchanged, but the new CNPC will control
all oil and gasfields, oil refineries, and petrochemical companies
in 12 provinces, autonomous regions, and municipalities, mainly in
northern and western China.
</P>
<P>
The new Sinopec will control oil and gasfields, oil refineries,
and petrochemical companies in 19 other provinces, autonomous
regions, and municipalities, mainly in the eastern and southern
parts of China.
</P>
<P>
CNPC will focus on exploration and production and Sinopec on
production of petrochemicals.
</P>
<P>
In keeping with its reform plans, a State Administration of the
Petroleum and Chemicals Industry has been set up based on the
former Ministry of the Chemicals Industry, CNPC and Sinopec, and
is directly under State Economic and Trade Commission jurisdiction.
</P>
<P>
Analysts predict that the two oil giants will be among the
world's top 500 companies in sales.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
