<HEADLINE> Ex-servicemen Finding Jobs in the Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 29 (Xinhua) -- China's ex-servicemen are trying to
find jobs in the market instead of being assigned by concerned
government departments.
</P>
<P>
To date, nearly 300 ex-servicemen have found jobs through the
labor market in Qingdao, a city in east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
This is the result of a method developed this year by the
Shandong Provincial Labor Bureau of arranging jobs for
ex-servicemen, which provides freedom for them to choose jobs and
freedom for work units to employ workers.
</P>
<P>
Many work units say they employ ex-servicemen because they
think that ex-servicemen are hard workers.
</P>
<P>
However, government assignments will still be the main method
of arranging jobs for ex-servicemen for the near future, according
to sources from the Shandong Provincial Labor Bureau.  
</P>
