<HEADLINE> BOC to Help Housing Items </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China (BOC) pledged
to provide six billion yuan (722 million US dollars) in loans to
the Famous Brand Construction and Development Co Ltd under a
Ministry of Construction program designed to speed up construction
of experimental residential quarters this year, today's "China
Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
It is the largest loan agreement ever between a Chinese
commercial bank and a real estate company.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Construction started construction of
experimental residential quarters in 1989. By March, the ministry
had built more than 400 residential quarters in more than 300
cities across China.
</P>
<P>
According to bank sources, BOC will increase its proportion of
real estate sector loans by two percentage points each year,
raising the rate to 8 percent from the current 3.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The proportional increase means that BOC's outstanding loans
for the real estate sector will soon increase from 20 billion yuan
(2.41 billion US dollars) to 56 billion yuan (6.75 billion US
dollars).
</P>
<P>
BOC, China's major foreign exchange bank, budgeted 11 billion
yuan (1.33 billion US dollars) in loans for housing construction
and consumption this year. The figure is 18 percent of the bank's
increased loans for 1998.
</P>
<P>
Lending priority will be given to ordinary residential housing
construction and to real estate projects now under construction,
the paper reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
