<HEADLINE> Italian Media Hail China as Leading Force for World Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The Italian media gave wide coverage
to U.S. President Bill Clinton's tour of China over the weekend,
saying China, with its importance growing in the international
arena, is a leading force for peace and stability in Asia and the
world.
</P>
<P>
Leading newspapers, news agencies, radios and TV stations
across the country devoted lengthy and detailed reports to the
summit between Clinton and his Chinese counterpart Jiang Zemin on
Saturday and the following press conference.
</P>
<P>
Eye-catching headlines accompanied by large photos depicting
Clinton's China visit appeared on the front pages of almost all
Italian newspapers.
</P>
<P>
The media and public opinion here are of the view that
improvement of Sino-U.S. relations, with its significance reaching
beyond a bilateral framework, not only benefits the two countries
concerned but also contributes to the peace and stability in the
region and the world at large.
</P>
<P>
Italy's top economic daily Il Sole-24 Ore, leading national
newspapers Corriere della Sera and La Repubblica, and ANSA news
agency all prominently highlighted China's renewed promise not to
devalue its currency RMB.
</P>
<P>
Their reports said Beijing's pledge reflects its economic
strength and confidence, marking the stability of its currency and
the entire financial market.
</P>
<P>
Noting a stable RMB was making valuable contribution to the
financial order in Asia and even the world, the reports said
China's enormous efforts helped the world avert a financial crisis
that had once threatened to go out of control.
</P>
<P>
An economically developed and powerful China is a leading force
in maintaining stability and security in the world and in Asia in
particular, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the Sino-U.S. agreement on stop targeting their
nuclear missiles against each other, the Italian media said the
accord laid a solid foundation for the prevention of a nuclear war
between the two countries and provided a reliable assurance for
world peace.
</P>
<P>
The reports hailed that the two countries have established a
"constructive strategic partnership" towards the 21st century,
turning a new leaf in the bilateral relations and striking a new
political balance in Asia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
