<HEADLINE> Golden Opportunity for Rail Car Manufactures in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Manufacturers of rolling stock for
mass transit have a golden opportunity with China planning to
construct more urban subways and light rail systems, according to
today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
To ease traffic congestion in large Chinese cities, the State
Council recently approved the construction of Shanghai Pearl Line
(Line 3), Metro Shenzhen and Guangzhou Metro Line 2. Meanwhile,
construction of other lines in Wuhan, Nanjing, Chongqing, Qingdao
and Dalian are expecting approval.
</P>
<P>
"Completion of these metro lines will demand a large number of
railway cars, which created a golden opportunity for us," said
Teng Maogen, vice-director of Changchun Car Co., the only railway
car supplier in China.
</P>
<P>
As the State Council has required a minimum of 60 percent local
content in construction of railway cars, the company has
established with the Europe-based ABB Daimler-Benz Transportation
GmbH the Changchun Adtranz Railway Vehicle Co. Ltd in Changchun.
</P>
<P>
The new joint venture will focus on local manufacturing,
assembly and testing of metro cars, light rail vehicles, multiple
units and aluminum car body shells. The annual production capacity
is planned at 160 vehicles, which are to supply the demand in
Shenzhen, Shanghai and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
Since the first metro was turned out in 1965, China has had 70
kilometers of subways operating in Beijing, Tianjin, Shanghai and
Guangzhou, according to China Railway Society Statistics. The
Changchun Car Co. has supplied all of China's domestically
produced 453 metro vehicles in Beijing and Tianjin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
