<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Opens First "Stroke Unit" in Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka opened the first medical
facility in the country to deal with strokes at the Colombo
National Hospital here Monday, according to medical sector
sources.
</P>
<P>
The stroke, an occasion when a blood tube in the brain suddenly
bursts or is blocked, is a major killer in Sri Lanka and in fact,
it is the country's second leading cause of death, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The Stroke Unit of the Colombo National Hospital will have a
multi-disciplinary team of health care professionals, a team that
specializes in and is dedicated to stroke care, attached to it.
</P>
<P>
The stroke unit is headed by Consultant Neurologist Dr. Jagath
Wijesekera, the sources added. 
</P>
