<HEADLINE> President Clinton Vows to Promote U.S.-China Partnership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Visiting U.S. President Bill
Clinton said here today that he will do his job to build good
relations between the United States and China, which is in the
interest of the American people rather than containing China.
</P>
<P>
When asked by a class 1997 student after his address at
Beijing University this morning whether he has a "secret design"
behind his smile to the Chinese people, Clinton said: "No, I don't."
</P>
<P>
"You ask me if we really want to contain China. The answer is
'no'," he told Chinese and American audience in a stadium in
Beijing University.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that it will be far better for the people of the
United States to have a partnership on equal, respectful terms
with China in the 21st century than to have to spend enormous
amount of time and money trying to contain China because we
disagree with what's going on," he said.
</P>
<P>
"So I do not want it (to contain China). I want a partnership
(between the two countries. So I am not having another design
behind my smile. It's what I really believe," he said.
</P>
<P>
"If you look at American people," he added, "they always have a
warm feeling toward China."
</P>
<P>
"If you go back to the history of our country, there's
always been a feeling on the part of our people that we ought to
be close to the Chinese people," President Clinton said.
</P>
