<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Aircraft Crash-lands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- All the seven people, including two
passengers, on aboard a 19-seat aircraft of Bangladesh's private
Air Parabat survived on Sunday when the plane crash-landed near
the capital.
</P>
<P>
The plane bound for Dhaka from Ishurdi in Pabna district, some
140 kilometers northwest of here, made an emergency landing on a
jute field at Savar on the outskirts of the capital, with the two
passengers suffering only minor injuries, press reports said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The injured were given first aid at Savar hospital and were
released later.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at about 11:40 a.m. local time due to a
technical fault in the engine when the Czech-made L-410 aircraft
was approaching the Dhaka Airport, a company official was quoted
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The domestic airlines has decided to suspend its operation for
15 days after the accident, the official added.
</P>
<P>
A four-member inquiry committee has started investigating the
accident, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Air Parabat, which started operation in January this year, is
one of the three private domestic airlines in Bangladesh. 
</P>
