<HEADLINE> Beijing University Welcomes U.S. President (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Extensive international exchanges
and cooperation are the motive force for the constant progress
Beijing University has made.
</P>
<P>
Chen Jia'er, president of Beijing University, one of China's
oldest and most prestigious institutions of higher learning, said
this in his speech welcoming U.S. President Bill Clinton this
morning.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. President, who is on a nine-day state visit to China,
visited the University, also known as Beida, this morning, and is
expected to deliver a speech at the campus.
</P>
<P>
Chen said that students and faculty of Beijing University
have always been paying close attention to the development of the
Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
"We are pleased to see that President Clinton is paying a
successful visit to China following Chinese President Jiang
Zemin's successful state visit to the U.S. last fall," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We sincerely hope that China and the U.S. will continue their
efforts to make even greater contributions to world peace,
stability and prosperity in the 21st century," he said.
</P>
<P>
Chen added that Chinese President Jiang inspected the
university two months ago and made an important speech.
</P>
<P>
"Today, We're very glad to see that President Clinton and his
wife and official delegation, have come to visit our school, and
will also make an important speech here," he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that patriotism, progress, democracy and science
constitute the fine tradition of the university, which just
celebrated the centenary of its founding early last month.
</P>
</TEXT>
