<HEADLINE> Qingdao to Sponsor International Beer Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- An international beer festival
will be held in this port city in east China's Shandong Province
on July 8-23.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 breweries from across the world, including
Holland, Australia, Singapore, Denmark, Mexico, Germany, Belgium,
the United States and the Republic of Korea, are expected to take
part in the fair, the eighth in Qingdao.
</P>
<P>
The organizing committee said that beer brewing experts from
Holland, Germany, the United States and Japan will give lectures
on beer-brewing techniques and equipment.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 1.12 million Chinese and foreign tourists flocked to
the fair, gulping down 496,000 liters of beer. 
</P>
