<HEADLINE> Britain and Russia Retain Euro Cup Athletics Titles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Britain and Russia retained the
men's and women's titles respectively of the European Cup
athletics tournament which ended in St Petersburg, Russia on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The British men's team collected a total of 111 points, 2.5
ahead of Germany, ensuring them a berth in the World Cup in
Johannesburg in September.
</P>
<P>
This is the third time Britain has broken the Russian and
German dominance of the competition.
</P>
<P>
Russia won the women's competition -- their seventh Cup triumph
-- when they defeated Germany by 124 points to 108.
</P>
<P>
Men's athlete of the meeting was Colin Jackson, who won the
110 meters hurdles in a world-class 13.17 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Italy's Fiona May took the women's award, the only athlete to
win two golds at the tourney.
</P>
<P>
May wrested the triple jump gold and set a new Italian
record of 7.08 meters in the long jump. 
</P>
</TEXT>
