<HEADLINE> China's Electric Appliance Conglomerate Competes Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Qingdao Haier Group Co., one of
China's largest electrical appliance manufacturers, has made
remarkable progress in its overseas operations, according to Zhang
Ruimin, group president.
</P>
<P>
The products of this group have been exported to more than 70
countries and regions and its brand " Haier" registered in 128
countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The group earned 56 million U.S. dollars from exports last
year, and in the first five months of this year its export volume
increased by 60 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
To get a firm foothold in the global market, Haier has
developed more than 30 exclusive dealerships and 9,000
distributors abroad.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the group has also set up factories in the
Philippines, Indonesia, Malaysia and Yugoslavia. 
</P>
