<HEADLINE> French Captain Demands Tougher Approach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LENS, June 28 (Xinhua) -- French team captain Dider Deschamps
demanded his teammates to get tough after they beat Paraguay 1-0
with a golden goal.
</P>
<P>
The goal was scored by Laurent Blanc in the "sudden death" extra
time after the two teams played to a goalless tie after the
regulation time.
</P>
<P>
"We had to dig deeper into our reserves at the end. We used up a
lot of energy today. I finished with terrible cramp." said Deschamps.
</P>
<P>
"We have to be a lot tougher against Italy because that's going
to be something else. Playing Italy is going to be very difficult."
the French captain said.
</P>
<P>
Youri Djorkaeff said France had equal talent to the Italian
team:"I could not care less about the Italians. Italians, Brazilians
and Germans, I'm not thinking about them. I'm thinking about the
French team."
</P>
<P>
French coach Aime Jacquet said his team deserved the win:"They
wanted to defend and exploit any space we left them and we had to
work really hard to get where we ended up."
</P>
<P>
"Considering our enormous domination, the victory was logical,"
said Jacquet, "We are still en route to be the world champions. We
just have to take it one game at a time." Jacquet said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
